n: center;\"><em><strong>* ⁠Mayte Caamal ( Viol&iacute;n )&nbsp;</strong></em><br><em><strong>* ⁠Eduardo V&aacute;squez ( Viol&iacute;n )&nbsp;</strong></em><br><em><strong>* ⁠Jos&iacute;as S&aacute;nchez ( Viola )&nbsp;</strong></em><br><em><strong>⁠+ Invitados</strong></em></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"writing-block-editor markdown-new-styling relative flow-root pt-(--writing-block-editor-pt) pe-(--writing-block-editor-pr) pb-(--writing-block-editor-pb) ps-(--writing-block-editor-pl)\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<div class=\"ProseMirror markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full min-h-6 break-words focus:outline-none\" dir=\"auto\" contenteditable=\"true\" translate=\"no\" data-writing-block-fullscreen-editor-region=\"true\" data-writing-block-fullscreen-editor-layout=\"inline\" aria-disabled=\"false\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div contenteditable=\"false\"><hr></div>\n<p>For this edition, we present <strong>The Beatles Tribute Edition</strong>, an intimate live concert celebrating the timeless music of one of the most influential bands in history through a fresh and elegant acoustic interpretation.</p>\n<p>Blending voice and live instrumentation, the evening revisits some of The Beatles' most iconic songs, inviting guests on a nostalgic journey through melodies that have transcended generations. Designed as a candlelit experience, the concert creates a warm and immersive atmosphere where music, emotion, and connection take center stage.</p>\n<p>The experience takes place at Vesica Santuario, a space designed for connection, presence, and immersion in nature &mdash; where music becomes part of the environment, accompanied by a curated food and beverage offering available throughout the evening.</p>\n<div contenteditable=\"false\"><hr></div>\n<p><strong><em>Program Highlights</em></strong></p>\n<p><em>* Let it be (Lennon/McCartney)</em><br><em>* ⁠Blackbird (Lennon/McCartney)</em><br><em>* ⁠Something (G.Harrison)&nbsp;</em><br><em>* ⁠Here comes the sun (G Harrison)</em></p>\n<p><strong>and more...</strong></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"475\" data-end=\"750\"><em><img src=\"https://ttf-public.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/ksAsNojlncc3Y7dJqkmW3QRl4kOZcA1eu9oIFJpRFzwts3y3582BdcvDQF3uNpbR.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"941\" height=\"1672\"></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"475\" data-end=\"750\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"80\" data-end=\"519\"><strong><em>Important Information</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>- Doors open prior to the concert start time</em><br data-start=\"128\" data-end=\"131\"><em>- Please arrive on time for check-in at the concierge to ensure a smooth entry</em><br data-start=\"211\" data-end=\"214\"><em>- We kindly ask guests to respect the silence and atmosphere during the performance</em><br data-start=\"300\" data-end=\"303\"><em>- Guest list tickets are valid only within their designated time</em><br data-start=\"385\" data-end=\"388\"><em>- Late arrivals may be subject to availability or require a ticket upgrade</em><br data-start=\"465\" data-end=\"468\"><em>- Seating is limited and varies by ticket type</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>- Contact: +52 984 323 9572 / reservations@vesicatulum.com</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>",
          "description": "The Beatles Tribute Edition\n\n* Manuel Negrete ( Cello )\n* â Mayte Caamal ( Violín )\n* â Eduardo Vásquez ( Violín )\n* â Josías Sánchez ( Viola )\nâ + Invitados\n\n---------------------------------------------------------------\n\nFor this edition, we present The Beatles Tribute Edition, an intimate live concert celebrating the timeless music of one of the most influential bands in history through a fresh and elegant acoustic interpretation.\n\nBlending voice and live instrumentation, the evening revisits some of The Beatles' most iconic songs, inviting guests on a nostalgic journey through melodies that have transcended generations. Designed as a candlelit experience, the concert creates a warm and immersive atmosphere where music, emotion, and connection take center stage.\n\nThe experience takes place at Vesica Santuario, a space designed for connection, presence, and immersion in nature — where music becomes part of the environment, accompanied by a curated food and beverage offering available throughout the evening.\n---------------------------------------------------------------\n\nProgram Highlights\n\n* Let it be (Lennon/McCartney)\n* â Blackbird (Lennon/McCartney)\n* â Something (G.Harrison)\n* â Here comes the sun (G Harrison)\n\nand more...\n\nImportant Information\n\n- Doors open prior to the concert start time\n- Please arrive on time for check-in at the concierge to ensure a smooth entry\n- We kindly ask guests to respect the silence and atmosphere during the performance\n- Guest list tickets are valid only within their designated time\n- Late arrivals may be subject to availability or require a ticket upgrade\n- Seating is limited and varies by ticket type\n\n- Contact: +52 984 323 9572 / reservations@vesicatulum.com\n\n-",
